From fd35d48f7aa61743e8265994cc2e4d2527241d41 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Locietta <locietta@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 21:01:32 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] hv_sock: fix stale recv_desc handling in hvs_stream_has_data()

Nevuly/WSL2-Rolling-Kernel-Issue#42 reports an issue about stdin
redirection from Windows to Linux (e.g., `echo hi | wsl -u root sh`)
silently fails and returns error code 1.

We have a quick fix by
https://github.com/Nevuly/WSL2-Linux-Kernel-Rolling/commit/95e754d76d299db54f2e8a7075bb1cd29bbc02c5.
While it does work, it brings more potential side effect.

I find a new issue that prevents me from calling .exe inside WSL2
after the patch. The issue is not reliably reproducible though. It
may or may not disappear after a reboot of WSL2.

When recv_desc points at a packet that has already been fully drained,
hvs_stream_has_data() must advance the iterator before reporting payload.

The previous workaround of returning a synthetic positive byte count
fixes the stdin pipe regression, but it misreports stream state to
other hvsock users. WSL interop uses blocking framed control messages
on hvsock channels, so that fake readability can surface as unexpected
EOF or protocol breakage. So in rare cases, the exe interop between WSL2
and Windows host will break.

Advance recv_desc with hv_pkt_iter_next() when the current descriptor
has already been consumed, otherwise refill from hv_pkt_iter_first().
If the iterator reaches the end of the ring, treat that as iterator
completion / EOF rather than -ENOBUFS. This preserves the stdin pipe
fix while keeping receive semantics correct for other hvsock clients.

Test: Build and type `echo echo hi |  wsl -u root sh` in Windows CMD
Signed-off-by: Locietta <locietta@gmail.com>
---
 net/vmw_vsock/hyperv_transport.c | 13 +++++++------
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/vmw_vsock/hyperv_transport.c b/net/vmw_vsock/hyperv_transport.c
index 432fcbbd1..1dc531f7b 100644
--- a/net/vmw_vsock/hyperv_transport.c
+++ b/net/vmw_vsock/hyperv_transport.c
@@ -694,7 +694,6 @@ static ssize_t hvs_stream_enqueue(struct vsock_sock *vsk, struct msghdr *msg,
 static s64 hvs_stream_has_data(struct vsock_sock *vsk)
 {
 	struct hvsock *hvs = vsk->trans;
-	bool need_refill;
 	s64 ret;
 
 	if (hvs->recv_data_len > 0)
@@ -702,11 +701,13 @@ static s64 hvs_stream_has_data(struct vsock_sock *vsk)
 
 	switch (hvs_channel_readable_payload(hvs->chan)) {
 	case 1:
-		need_refill = !hvs->recv_desc;
-		if (!need_refill)
-			return -EIO;
-
-		hvs->recv_desc = hv_pkt_iter_first(hvs->chan);
+		if (hvs->recv_desc) {
+			hvs->recv_desc = hv_pkt_iter_next(hvs->chan, hvs->recv_desc);
+			if (!hvs->recv_desc)
+				return 0;
+		} else {
+			hvs->recv_desc = hv_pkt_iter_first(hvs->chan);
+		}
 		if (!hvs->recv_desc)
 			return -ENOBUFS;
 
